comments[7]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-18T05:54:11.258Z",codex-sdk-vcs-20260718,"Implementation start 2026-07-18: dependencies pm-3mna and pm-cbwg are live-verified closed. This wide lane will build the package against public SDK exports only, exercise custom schema/statuses, commands/hooks, attributable history replay, and produce a structured gap report plus packed temp-workspace proof."
  "2026-07-18T07:17:34.514Z",codex-sdk-vcs-20260718,"Acceptance evidence 2026-07-18: @unbrained/pm-vcs ships 2 domain types, 4 fields, a custom commits_to ontology, VCS profile/workflow, 7 domain commands, reviewed-merge hook, point-in-time history reconstruction, and durable merge-ledger projection using public SDK contracts only. Linked tests pass 2/2. Packed manual proof installed the tarball into an isolated project, installed vcs, applied its profile, created/proposed/merged a changeset, reconstructed version 1, replayed version=1/processed=1 identically across fresh processes, passed isolated package doctor and tracker validation, and preserved normal core create/get."
  "2026-07-18T07:48:06.147Z",codex-sdk-vcs-20260718,"Pre-push Greptile corrections: VCS merge events now use stable merge-<changeset> identities and append without a stale read-then-write expectedVersion window, so concurrent independent merges serialize under the durable store lock. Installed SDK-dispatch acceptance proves packed-sdk-author reaches the immutable ledger; direct-source acceptance runs two independent merges concurrently."
  "2026-07-18T08:08:44.185Z",codex-sdk-vcs-20260718,"Pre-push Greptile re-review against committed head d37d6be9 completed clean at confidence 5/5 with zero comments. It explicitly verified end-to-end SDK author attribution, writer-lock serialization of concurrent independent VCS merges, strict relationship-kind registration validation with nested schema preservation, and the documented empty stream checkpoint boundary."
  "2026-07-18T08:31:15.850Z",codex-sdk-vcs-20260718,"Release-gate Greptile run cc0177cd-e16c-4bf8-9a4e-8fa900447367 found one P1 two-store partial-write risk in vcs merge. The correction implements a deterministic reconciliation protocol rather than a line-order swap: an existing matching ledger event finalizes a proposed item, a matching merged item can restore a missing ledger event, and conflicting deterministic events fail closed. Failure-injection acceptance covers ledger-first, item-first, and conflict states. Full repository coverage passes 308 files / 5,893 tests at exact 100/100/100/100; focused typecheck and ESLint pass."
  "2026-07-18T08:40:48.922Z",codex-sdk-vcs-20260718,"Targeted post-fix Greptile re-review against b8b40b51 completed at confidence 5/5 with zero comments. It confirms both partial-write directions recover correctly, deterministic conflicts fail closed, concurrent independent merges remain serialized, author attribution remains intact, and the failure-injection tests meaningfully exercise the durable protocol."
  "2026-07-18T09:25:20.389Z",codex-root,"Hosted review round 1 evidence: implemented all valid Gemini and CodeRabbit findings across legacy activation compatibility, graph/loader compatibility documentation, VCS ref validation, event-first crash reconciliation, package report routing, global runtime cleanup, and temporary-ledger cleanup. Added explicit strict-contract rejection coverage for missing ordering and allowSelf because these fields are required by the public RelationshipKindDefinition contract; defaulting them would conceal malformed JavaScript or JSON extension input. Full sandbox coverage passed: 308 files, 5,896 tests, exact 100/100/100/100 (38,758 statements; 27,272 branches; 7,884 functions; 37,746 lines)."
notes[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-18T07:17:35.726Z",codex-sdk-vcs-20260718,"Gap disposition: production content-addressed object storage, tree diffing, and network transport are VCS-product concerns, not universal SDK gaps. Cross-item plus relationship atomic commit remains an explicit bounded-exemplar waiver; larger durable indexing and scale work stays on canonical pm-ju83/pm-m2il lineage."
learnings[2]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-18T07:17:35.117Z",codex-sdk-vcs-20260718,"A foreign-domain package can remain core-independent when the host injects lifecycle, history, and relationship services. Runtime package imports stay type-only; values come from context.sdk, allowing bundled installed copies to execute without private paths or nested CLI resolution."
  "2026-07-18T07:48:06.788Z",codex-sdk-vcs-20260718,"For durable domain commands, do not read currentVersion and then reacquire the append lock merely to supply that version: the gap creates avoidable conflicts across independent mutations. Omit the optional OCC precondition when the store lock itself defines serialization, and use a stable domain event id for duplicate detection."
