body: "# Spike — minimal VCS-style changeset workflow as a pm package\n\nBuild a small, throwaway-quality but end-to-end **exemplar package** that models a version-control-like domain purely on public pm SDK primitives: a `Changeset` custom type with a domain status graph (draft → proposed → merged/abandoned), `ref`/`branch` modeled as custom fields or link relations, domain verbs (`propose`, `merge`, `abandon`) as extension-registered commands, merge rules enforced by hooks, and domain state derived by replaying the audited history stream.\n\n## Why\nThis is the acceptance vehicle for the beyond-PM platform story (parent epic pm-usfg): the vision claims one could build \"a VCS like Git or a company's business logic\" on the SDK. A spike either demonstrates that with today's primitives or produces a precise, itemized gap list.\n\n## Deliverables\n- Exemplar package (sandbox or packages/ exemplar, mirroring the pm-cbwg / pm-kanban archetype pattern) importing ONLY the public SDK (`src/sdk`), zero private core imports (boundary ratchet pm-8778 applies).\n- A written gap report: every place the spike needed a workaround, filed as individual dedupe-checked SDK items under pm-usfg.\n- Smoke test in a temp workspace proving create → propose → merge → history-replay round-trip.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\nSpike package activates cleanly; the changeset workflow round-trip passes in a sandbox smoke; gap report exists with each gap either filed as a pm item or explicitly waived; no private core imports.\n\n## Sequencing\nDepends on pm-cbwg (PM-domain exemplar first) and pm-3mna (schema/config primitives in the SDK)."
